{{Infobox ethnic group |group = Filipinos in Pakistan |image= |population = 3,000 |popplace = [[Islamabad]], [[Karachi]], [[Lahore]] |langs = [[Tagalog language|Tagalog]], [[English language|English]], other [[languages of the Philippines]], [[Urdu]] |rels = [[Christianity]], [[Islam]] |related-c = [[Filipino people]], [[Overseas Filipinos]] }}
'''Filipinos in Pakistan''' ({{lang-ur|فَلپائنی}}) consist of migrants from the [[Philippines]]. In 2008, an estimated 3,000 work as [[domestic workers]],<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.monstersandcritics.com/news/southasia/news/article_1371134.php/Philippines_monitors_condition_of_Filipino_workers_in_Pakistan|archive-url=https://archive.is/20130103221927/http://www.monstersandcritics.com/news/southasia/news/article_1371134.php/Philippines_monitors_condition_of_Filipino_workers_in_Pakistan|dead-url=yes|archive-date=January 3, 2013|title=Philippines monitors condition of Filipino workers in Pakistan|date=Nov 5, 2007|publisher=M&C|accessdate=19 December 2009}}</ref> according to the statistics of the Philippine government. Many Filipino women came to Pakistan for work and those who later got married to Pakistani men are now holding Pakistani citizenship.<ref name="BusinessMirror">{{cite news |url=http://www.businessmirror.com.ph/0509&102008/headlines08.html |title=New Pakistan PM getting Filipino helpers |first=Lyn Resurreccion |date=May 9, 2008 |publisher=BusinessMirror |accessdate=19 December 2009 |location=Islamabad, Pakistan |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20081123063550/http://www.businessmirror.com.ph/0509%26102008/headlines08.html |archivedate=November 23, 2008 |df= }}</ref> Pakistan comparatively has experience good immigration rate from Philippines despite of security issues.
==Migration history== Many Filipino people entered Pakistan's commercial center [[Karachi]] illegally with fake passports and false identity cards as early in 1990s along with hundreds of [[Nepal]]i, Bengals, [[Sri Lankans]] and [[India]]ns<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.outlookindia.com/article.aspx?200305|title=Homeless In Karachi|last=Owais Tohid, Arshad Mahmud |date=November 1995|publisher=Outlook India|accessdate=9 January 2010}}</ref> however later deported. As of April 2010, there are 546 registered Filipino living in Pakistan who were eligible to vote in [[2010 Philippine presidential election]] as per Philippines Foreign Affairs ministry.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.dfa.gov.ph/main/index.php/news-from-rp-embassies/972-philippine-embassy-in-islamabad-begins-overseas-absentee-polls|title=Philippine Embassy in Islamabad Begins Overseas Absentee Polls|date=April 10, 2010|publisher=MoFA|accessdate=3 September 2010}}</ref>
== Employment == Many Filipinos in Pakistan are domestic workers, including the housemaids of high government officials and rich Pakistanis. There are some three Filipino maids at house of former [[Prime Minister of Pakistan|Pakistani Prime Minister]] [[Yousaf Raza Gillani]] and many Filipinos working as chefs in Japanese restaurants in [[Karachi]]<ref name="BusinessMirror"/> and [[Islamabad]]. A small number of Filipinos studying [[Islam]] in the country is reported by the Philippines Embassy in Islamabad<ref>{{cite journal|author=Dante|date=June 6, 2008|title=Why Pakistan matters to the Philippines |url=http://www.manilatimes.net/national/2008/june/06/yehey/opinion/20080606opi7.html}}</ref> while thousands of Muslim students from various Southeast Asian countries including Philippines illegally studying in the Pakistani [[Madrasah]]s. Some Filipinos are also [[Nursing in Pakistan|nurses in Pakistan]].
== Relations with Pakistani society == In 2007, following a state of emergency declared by Pakistani President [[Pervez Musharraf]], about 200 Filipinos gathered in Islamabad on the advice of Ambassador Jimmy Yambao to call for protest.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://globalnation.inquirer.net/news/breakingnews/view/20071105-98873/Arroyo_orders_tight_security_for_Filipinos_in_Pakistan|title=Arroyo orders tight security for Filipinos in Pakistan|first= Lira Dalangin-Fernandez, Veronica Uy|publisher=Agence France-Presse|accessdate=19 December 2009}}</ref> However, there have no direct threats to safety of Filipinos in Pakistan reported.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gmanews.tv/video/13805/no-direct-threats-to-pinoys-in-pakistan-dfa-assures|title=No direct threats to Pinoys in Pakistan, DFA assures|publisher=}}</ref>
