'''Storyani''' ({{lang-ps|ستورياني}}), also called '''Ustrani''' or '''Ustarana''', is a [[Pashtun people|Pashtun]] [[tribe]], they inhabit the [[Frontier regions|Frontier Region]] in the outer hills opposite the extreme south of [[Dera Ismail Khan]] district<ref name=EB1911>{{cite EB1911 |wstitle=Ustarana |volume=27 |page=811}}</ref> of [[Khyber Pakhtunkhwa Province]], [[Pakistan]]. They have occupied the eastern slope of [[Suleiman Mountains]]. To their north lies [[Gomal River]], which separates [[South Waziristan Agency]] from this region. To their south west across [[Baluchistan (Pakistan)|Baluchistan]] border is Zhob, to the east towards Daman plains with the [[Gandapurs]] of [[Kulachi]], to the west with [[Musakhel Bazar|Musa Khel]] and [[Zmaryani]] while [[Qaisrani]] (a [[Baloch people|Balouch]] tribe) on the south.<ref>Pashtun. (2007). In ''Encyclopædia Britannica''. Retrieved June 1, 2007, from Encyclopædia Britannica Online: http://www.britannica.com/eb/article-9058636</ref>
==History and origin== Until about the 18th century the Storyani were entirely a pastoral and trading tribe;<ref name=EB1911/> they were venturesome traders, carrying goods from [[Kandahar]] as far as [[West Bengal]], but the feud with their neighbors the [[Musakhel Bazar|Musa Khel]] and the [[Bozdar]] put a stop to their annual westward immigration, and they were forced to take to agriculture and subsequently acquired a good deal of the country below the hills.<ref name=EB1911/> Their territory includes the eastern slopes of the [[Suleiman Mountains]], the crest of the range being held by the Musa Khel, and Zmaryani.<ref name=EB1911/><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://archive.org/stream/frontieroverseas03indi/frontieroverseas03indi_djvu.txt|title=Full text of "Frontier and overseas expeditions from India"|website=archive.org|access-date=2016-04-12}}</ref>
A descendant of Storyani tribe settled among and married into the [[Shirani (Pashtun tribe)|Sherani]] tribe. Storyani are descendants of Sarban<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Th3Mu-_RwjQC&pg=PA222&dq=ustarana&lr=#v=onepage&q=ustarana&f=false|title=A Glossary of the Tribes and Castes of the Punjab and North-West Frontier Province: L.-Z|last=Rose|first=Horace Arthur|date=1997-01-01|publisher=Atlantic Publishers & Dist|isbn=9788185297705|language=en}}</ref> (Son of [[Qais Abdur Rashid]]).
