'''The People's Army Model''' ([[Hebrew]]: '''מודל צבא העם''') is a [[school of thought]] in Israel concerning the role of the Israeli Army, the [[Israel Defense Forces|IDF]], vis-à-vis Israeli society. According to this conception, the IDF plays a broader role than merely defending Israel's national security. It also has a social role in implementing the country's [[melting pot]] policy, through integrating all sectors of Israeli society into its units. Israel's [[regular army]] is relatively small, and thus its strength in emergency is based on [[reservists]], which comprise much of the entire nation.<ref>[http://jpress.org.il/Default/Scripting/ArticleWin.asp?From=Archive&Skin=TAUHe&BaseHref=DAV/1950/10/15&EntityId=Ar00102&ViewMode=HTML] [http://jpress.org.il/Default/Scripting/ArticleWin.asp?From=Archive&Skin=TAUHe&BaseHref=DAV/1951/11/25&EntityId=Ar00121&ViewMode=HTML]</ref> Following the [[Suez Crisis]], the Israeli newspaper ''[[Davar]]'' published the following: "Our army is, as is well known, the people's army, an army of reserves, the laborer and the clerk, [as] the laborer and the teacher had one day laid down their daily work and stabilized the flag".<ref>[http://jpress.org.il/Default/Scripting/ArticleWin.asp?From=Archive&Skin=TAUHe&BaseHref=DAV/1956/12/07&EntityId=Ar00302&ViewMode=HTML]</ref> It is from this premise that the view that the school is called to the training of youth to be the "people's army", by providing uniform education, was derived.<ref>[http://jpress.org.il/Default/Scripting/ArticleWin.asp?From=Archive&Skin=TAUHe&BaseHref=DAV/1949/04/03&EntityId=Ar00207&ViewMode=HTML]</ref>

